The paper proposes a method for improving the performance of Graph Convolution Networks (GCNs) for learning node representations on graphs. This is a problem that falls under the category of machine learning, specifically deep learning, which is covered by several sub-categories in arXiv CS. The paper focuses on improving the stability of GCNs by addressing the dimensional information imbalance of node representations. This is a problem that is relevant to several sub-categories, including cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CV (Computer Vision), cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), and cs.CL (Computation and Language). Therefore, these are the most likely sub-categories for this paper, ordered from most to least likely.
